                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the King; incipit of Text I;
                           incipit of the prayers to be read; directives to the ministers; words
                           yǝbärkäwwo (fols. 5ra-6rb) and nǝsǝʾǝläkä (fols. 18va-19va, 32rb-34ra);
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals. 
                           On the incipit page of Text I (fol. 3r), a few lines are rubricated
                           (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">ff. 1va-2</locus>
                           <desc>vb: Unidentified hymn in praise of God and other saints.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1va">1va</locus>: በዘዚአሁ፡ አርአያወ፡ አምሳል፡ ይትአኰት፡ ወይሴባሕ፡
                              ስሙ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Walatta Mikāʾel mentioned in the supplication
                           formula at the end of the text was probably linked to the first owner of
                           the Ms. (?) Walda Śǝllāse (s. Additio 3 and the supplication on <locus target="#35ra">35ra-</locus>
                           <note>rb). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#31va">f. 31va</locus>
                           <desc>: Note listing the names: King Yoḥannǝs (r. 1872-89), Metropolitan
                              ʾAtnatewos (in tenure 1869-76), śätätot (?) Giyorgis, priest (qasis )
                              Fāsiladas, and </desc>qes gabaz Kidāna Māryām.<quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#31va">31va</locus>: ንጉሥነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ጳጳስነ፡ አትና፡ ቴዎስ፡ ሠተቶት፡
                              ጊዎርጊስ[sic]፡ ወለቀሲ[ስ]ሒ፡ ፋሲለደስ፡ ወለ{ቄስ}፡ ገበዝሒ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Written in the same hand as that of the note
                           written on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>
                           <note> (s. Varia). It is unclear why the names were listed. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#31va">f. 31va</locus>
                           <desc>-vb: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#31va">31va</locus>: ለዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘተሣየጦ፡ በወርቁ፡ ወልደ፡ ሠላሴ፡
                              ወብእሲቱ፡ ፍሥሐ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወወለቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ከመ፡ ይኵኖሙ፡ መርሐ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ዘሠረቆ፡
                              ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ [<locus target="#31vb">31vb</locus>]
                              ለይኵን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note mentions the Ms. was bought by Walda Śǝllāse (his wife is
                              Fǝśśǝḥa Giyorgis, his daughter is Walatta Mikāʾel). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#31vb">f. 31vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#31vb">31vb</locus>: ለዘቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘተሳየጦ፡ ገብረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡
                              ወለተ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ገብረ፡ አምላክ፡ ወለተ፡ መድኅን። ወለደ፡ አናንያ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note mentions that Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer and other individuals
                              bought the Ms. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Short note ገብረ፡ ጊዎርጊስ፡ ወለዲያቆንሒ written in the same hand
                           that of Additio 2: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.
 - Doodles: <locus target="#35v">35v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
